         <abstract>
            <p>In the United Kingdom forecasts have been shown in prospectuses for many years. The author notes that prospective investors consider management's opinion on future profitability the most important single element bearing on their decision, and argues for extension of formal corporate forecasting to companies' periodic public reporting.</p>
